reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My new favorite compact tripod
reviews.reviewText: I just love this little tripod. I have several that I use with my GoPro cameras. Most are cheaply made of plastic and don't feel very sturdy in the hand. This one is well made, with sturdy materials, feels solid in the hand and looks like it will last for years with heavy use. Folded up it works great as a hand mount. Then it's very easy to deploy and set on the ground or a nearby table or rock to capture video. I shoot a lot of content in the outdoors on 4X4 trips. I will typically hike up the trail as vehicles are working their way through technical terrain. I keep my Nikon mirrorless camera on my strap to shoot stills while also filming with a GoPro to get video at the same time. This little tripod makes it quick and easy to set the GoPro up so it can keep rolling while I step away to shoot from a different angle. It's a handy thing to have in your kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Tabletop Camera Tripod
reviews.reviewText: I got my hands on the K&F Concept Metal Mini Phone Camera Tripod, and here's the lowdown: It's a lightweight champ, weighing just 208 grams, and it's compatible with cellphones, cameras—you name it! The adjustable height is a handy feature, with two levels to choose from. Plus, it's a universal fit for both iPhones and Androids, along with compact cameras.One cool perk is the Bluetooth remote that comes with it, making it a breeze to capture those group shots or solo adventures. It's even got your back if you're rocking a DSLR or micro four-thirds camera, handling up to 44 pounds like a pro.Now, let's talk downsides—the leg angles aren't adjustable, which might limit your angles a bit. Also, due to its small size, it's not as rock-steady as those big tripods out there.But here's the verdict: If you're all about portability and versatility, the K&F Concept MS05 Mini Metal Tripod is a solid choice. It pulls double duty as a mini tabletop tripod and a trusty handheld stabilizer. For the price, it's a smart investment for your camera gear. Whether you're a vlogger or just love getting up close and personal with your shots, this little guy has your back. 📸👍

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solidly made mini tripod for use on your desk or a table. Best for use with small cameras!
reviews.reviewText: I've only used this with my mirrorless APS-C camera so far and I've found it to be stable and sufficient to hold up the camera and a 30mm prime lens with ease. The build quality is excellent and seems like it'll handle being throw into a camera bag or backpack without any issues.It's cheap, affordable and well made so I would happily recommend this to others who want a small tripod like this!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Versatile Tripod Base
reviews.reviewText: I picked up the 13CM version of this stand to use with the K&F Selfie Stick (MS07) primarily as a mini-monopod with an OSMO Pocket 3. I was so impressed with the quality and height adjustability of the 13CM version that I purchased the 20CM version as well. The 20cm version came with the bonus of a phone mount and Bluetooth remote in the package which makes it a better value IMO. K&F was not a brand I was familiar with just a couple of years ago, but I have to say everything that I have acquired filters, accessories, and batteries have been of high quality and fit the application I was applying them to perfectly. Not only will these work with the Pocket 3 as intended, but the stands are sturdy enough to support a table-mounted mirrorless camera with a cage. It's rare that I receive something as a Vine reviewer and go out and purchase other complementary products from the same manufacturer. This decision was a "no brainer".

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very heavy duty all metal mini tripod. Not the most flexible with just two height configurations.
reviews.reviewText: Weight of the item is 169g, just as specified. All metal construction, save for the rubber leg ends, which are not too grippy, but will prevent scratching of surfaces. If you want to take a picture on a flat surface, this should handle a pretty large rig, the specs say up to 44 pounds. Balancing 44 lbs on this small tripod would be quite a feat.Could make for good use as a grip under a camera; as the legs fit together quite well when collapsed. I can see this working best for off camera flash / lighting, in my use cases. I suppose you could put a ball mount / other additional mount on top to give it more flexibility.For the price, it's a good buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Professional multipurpose metal mini tripod
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Professional multipurpose metal mini tripodRugged metal build with good no-slip silicone feet. There are thumb grooves that can release the legs so they can be used in a high or near-flat mode. The legs are broad giving it excellent stability.This is heavy-duty and can probably handle a significant amount of weight. It had no problem with my Sony FX3 camera but can certainly handle more than that. It's a multipurpose 1/4-inch screw that could hold anything from a gimbal to DSLR to light for tabletop shooting.This is most certainly a professional-grade mini tripod.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I’m really pleased with this sturdy, chunky, little tabletop tripod, which thanks to the curved leg design has a neat cylinder shape when closed for transport. This is lightweight, yet very robust feeling.The tripod has a standard screw fitment, and its load bearing capacity is plenty to accommodate my Panasonic Lumix S5IIXCE, even with a telephoto lens attached.The tripod comes with a couple of accessories: a useful phone holder attachment, and a Bluetooth remote (I’m less keen on this cheap-looking and -feeling little gadget).
